Build Instructions
==================
./configure && make

But if you want to hack on Last.fm, use ./configure --ide to get a nice project
file. Except on Linux, where you get Makefiles as usual. But everything good can
import those.

Build Requirements
==================
Windows
-------
cygwin -- tar, perl, ssh, svn, gzip, etc.
The latest Windows SDK
Qt 4.4 (built with Phonon support if you want sound)

Mac
---
Install macports, then install libmad, taglig, libsamplerate, libfftw3

./configure --release && make dmg

Folder Structure
================
dist/
  - tools for building distributible packages
